C. Kelly Wright https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C._Kelly_Wright 0 C. Kelly Wright is an actress, singer, and dancer. She has performed in Off-Broadway musicals and plays in New York City and in television and film in the U.S. and internationally. She is known for the development of new works in theater. She appeared in the world premieres of A Little Princess and Memphis. She has worked with new works from Marcus Gardley, Katori Hall, Imani Harrington, Mike Jones, Victor Lodato, Nina Mercer, Robert O'Hara, and Venus Opal Reese. She was an AUDELCO Award nominee for Best Supporting Actress. In film she is known for her performance in Black Nativity, Angel Wishes: Journey of a Spiritual Healer, and Everyday Black Man. Angel Wishes: Journey of a Spiritual Healer is based on the life of Lana Bettencourt, who survived childhood abuse and two abusive marriages. C._Kelly_Wright is an_actress , singer , and dancer .
